Name: CVE-2006-4935
Description: The Database module in Moodle before 1.6.2 does not properly handle uploaded files, which has unspecified impact and remote attack vectors.
References: CONFIRM:http://docs.moodle.org/en/Release_notes#Moodle_1.6.2

Name: CVE-2006-4936
Description: Moodle before 1.6.2 does not properly validate the module instance id when creating a course module object, which has unspecified impact and remote attack vectors.
References: CONFIRM:http://docs.moodle.org/en/Release_notes#Moodle_1.6.2

Name: CVE-2006-4937
Description: lib/setup.php in Moodle before 1.6.2 sets the error reporting level to 7 to display E_WARNING messages to users even if debugging is disabled, which might allow remote authenticated users to obtain sensitive information by triggering the messages.
References: CONFIRM:http://docs.moodle.org/en/Release_notes#Moodle_1.6.2

Name: CVE-2006-4938
Description: help.php in Moodle before 1.6.2 does not check the existence of certain help files before including them, which might allow remote authenticated users to obtain the path in an error message.
References: CONFIRM:http://docs.moodle.org/en/Release_notes#Moodle_1.6.2

Name: CVE-2006-4939
Description: backup/backup_scheduled.php in Moodle before 1.6.2 generates trace data with the full backup pathname even when debugging is disabled, which might allow attackers to obtain the pathname.
References: CONFIRM:http://docs.moodle.org/en/Release_notes#Moodle_1.6.2

Name: CVE-2006-4940
Description: login/forgot_password.php in Moodle before 1.6.2 allows remote attackers to obtain sensitive information (e-mail addresses and Moodle account names) via a find action.
References: CONFIRM:http://docs.moodle.org/en/Release_notes#Moodle_1.6.2

Name: CVE-2006-4941
Description: Multiple cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerabilities in Moodle before 1.6.2 might allow remote attackers to inject arbitrary web script or HTML via (1) the choose parameter in files/index.php and (2) the sub parameter in doc/index.php.
References: CONFIRM:http://docs.moodle.org/en/Release_notes#Moodle_1.6.2

Name: CVE-2006-4942
Description: Moodle before 1.6.2, when the configuration lacks (1) algebra or (2) tex filters, allows remote authenticated users to write LaTeX or MimeTeX output files to the top level of the dataroot directory via (a) filter/algebra/pix.php or (b) filter/tex/pix.php.
References: CONFIRM:http://docs.moodle.org/en/Release_notes#Moodle_1.6.2

Name: CVE-2006-4943
Description: course/jumpto.php in Moodle before 1.6.2 does not validate the session key (sesskey) before providing content from arbitrary local URIs, which allows remote attackers to obtain sensitive information via the jump parameter.
References: CONFIRM:http://docs.moodle.org/en/Release_notes#Moodle_1.6.2

Name: CVE-2006-4944
Description: PHP remote file inclusion vulnerability in includes/pear/Net/DNS/RR.php in ProgSys 0.151 and earlier allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary PHP code via a URL in the phpdns_basedir parameter.
References: BID:20141   |   URL:http://www.securityfocus.com/bid/20141   |   EXPLOIT-DB:2411   |   URL:https://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/2411   |   XF:progsys-rr-file-include(29078)   |   URL:https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/vulnerabilities/29078

Name: CVE-2006-4945
Description: Multiple PHP remote file inclusion vulnerabilities in Cardway (aka Frederic Boudaud) DigitalWebShop 1.128 and earlier allow remote attackers to execute arbitrary PHP code via a URL in the _PHPLIB[libdir] parameter to (1) rechnung.php or (2) prepend.php.
References: BID:20107   |   URL:http://www.securityfocus.com/bid/20107   |   EXPLOIT-DB:2398   |   URL:https://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/2398   |   SECUNIA:22026   |   URL:http://secunia.com/advisories/22026   |   VUPEN:ADV-2006-3705   |   URL:http://www.vupen.com/english/advisories/2006/3705   |   XF:digitalwebshop-libdir-file-include(29037)   |   URL:https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/vulnerabilities/29037

Name: CVE-2006-4946
Description: PHP remote file inclusion vulnerability in include/startup.inc.php in CMSDevelopment Business Card Web Builder (BCWB) 0.99, and possibly 2.5 Beta and earlier, allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary PHP code via a URL in the root_path parameter.

Name: CVE-2006-4981
Description: Symantec Sygate NAC allows physically proximate attackers to bypass control methods and join a local network by selecting a forged MAC address associated with an exception rule that (1) permits all non-Windows devices or (2) whitelists certain sets of Organizationally Unique Identifiers (OUIs).
References: BUGTRAQ:20060919 White paper release: Bypassing network access control (NAC) systems   |   URL:http://www.securityfocus.com/archive/1/446421/100/0/threaded   |   MISC:http://www.insightix.com/files/pdf/Bypassing_NAC_Solutions_Whitepaper.pdf

Name: CVE-2006-4982
Description: Cisco NAC maintains an exception list that does not record device properties other than MAC address, which allows physically proximate attackers to bypass control methods and join a local network by spoofing the MAC address of a different type of device, as demonstrated by using the MAC address of a disconnected printer.

Name: CVE-2006-4983

Name: CVE-2006-5035
Description: Multiple cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerabilities in Paul Smith Computer Services vCAP 1.7.0 allow remote attackers to inject arbitrary web script or HTML via (1) the statusmsg parameter in RegisterPage.cgi or (2) a URI corresponding to a nonexistent file. NOTE: the provenance of this information is unknown; the details are obtained from third party information.

Name: CVE-2006-5036
Description: ** DISPUTED **  MySource Matrix 3.8 and earlier, and MySource 2.x, allow remote attackers to use the application as an HTTP proxy server via the sq_remote_page_url parameter to access arbitrary sites with the server's IP address and conduct cross-site scripting (XSS) attacks. NOTE: the researcher reports that "The vendor does not consider this a vulnerability."

Name: CVE-2006-5037
Description: ** DISPUTED **  MySource Matrix after 3.8 allows remote attackers to use the application as an HTTP proxy server via a MIME encoded URL in the sq_content_src parameter to access arbitrary sites with the server's IP address and conduct cross-site scripting (XSS) attacks.  NOTE: the researcher reports that "The vendor does not consider this a vulnerability."
